title: Show HN: Lexverse – Find the Gems You're Looking for in Lex Fridman's Podcasts
text:
This was a cool project. I took the youtube transcripts of Lex Fridman's podcast, created embeddings, stored them on Pinecone and served them via fly.io.

I wanted to see if I could develop an app around semantic search. Originally was going to use OpenAI's new model but ended up using something lighter (I might change it up to see if there is a significant improvement).

title: Show HN: I built a simple, hackable Google Home replacement fully in Rust
text:
Fully built in Rust (Yew, Cursive, Rocket, RustEmbed, Sled)
 Easily extensible
 Compiles to single binary
 Only needs a Raspberry Pi Zero (or others) and a 15$ display
 Widgets can be configured by the user via a web interface
